<br>
the state of the warrior topic, is dealing with how, due to weapons/gear, AA, class balancing is affecting the role of the warrior. <br>
<br>
we are there to be able to get enough aggro to let the rest of our guild/group beat the shiznet out of the mob. we are to hold that aggrowell enough that it is not seriously handicapping the rest of the guild. and be able to take the beating that the same aggro delivers to us. whether this is by low dam/delay weaps, or weapons that proc very high aggro spells, or proc direct hate/aggro. and the defensiveness comes only from our armor/hp, and the occasional use of defensive or evasive. <br>
<br>
the complaint, is that we gave up the ability to cast spells. we focussed only on martial ability to be able to do our job. our job has been seriously encroached upon by other classes. this has diminished our class. we are trying to figure out suggestions that are reasonable and practical to implement to allow us to regain our role in the game as the &quot;master of combat&quot; as defined by verant's own class description.<br>
<br>
