<br>
So basically, you have trouble finding an XP group. Welcome to the world of EQ. All classes have that problem at one time or another. I would love for my Warrior to have some cool skills to bring to the group (through AA). But it aint gonna happen. My Ranger brings more utility, and gets groups because of the need for utility. A class is desired more than another based on what the group already has, or what the group needs. It isn't a conspiracy to push one class out of EQ for another. Have a Druid/Shammy as healer in the group? Best to have a Warrior MA over a Ranger, or an SK over both (for self-heals).  Have a Cleric, let any of them MA depending on what you wanna do. Sometimes I MA when we have a Warrior/Cleric, cuz Tank can stay at low health for crippling blows.  I can hold mob off his low health agro. Fun stuff. See? Its all situational. I have a thousand other scenarios I have seen with different MA's for different reasons in XP grinds, but I already have rambled too long.<br>
<br>
To sum up, the state of the Warrior is just fine for its functionality. The state of Players is something else entirely. If nobody wants you in thier group, make your own! I had to back in the Kunark-Rangers-suck era. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
