<br>
Hybrids had to deal with suckage for quite a long time when Kunark came out.<br>
<br>
Warriors got discs, obviously defensive being the best. They got improved offensive skills, they got improved defensive skills.<br>
Hybrids got jack. Offensive/defensive skills were hardly raised, they got no discs, and few new spells that were actually useful. Hybrids could hardly even solo back then (from what I read on the PoN board. I was still in the 'teens when Velious came out (I level very very slowly, only level 54 now), and didn't get a chance to see for myself).<br>
<br>
Out comes Velious. Hybrids actually get a few useful spells and a few useless discs. Not terribly useful, but they made a tiny difference. It still wasn't enough to balance out the Defense/Offense/Weapon skills/exp penalty they sacrificed for casting skills. <br>
<br>
Sometime during Velious, plate hybrids got a much needed Defense skill increase. Warriors recieved few improvements, but they were still clearly ahead.<br>
<br>
Also during Velious, 2hers recieved a better damage bonus, and the ratio on some were improved. 2hers could now occasionally outaggro or outdamage dual wielding. (1hers were never a good option for hybrids, since there is no option to dual wield, so this 2h improvement was needed.) However, Warriors could and can still use almost every single 2her that Hybrids could, all the way from Arbiter's Combine Greatsword in Kunark to Goldenrod in Luclin, so this also benefitted them.<br>
<br>
Luclin comes out. Everyone recieves boosts with AA and new Luclin gear; Hybrids got the most benefit from AA because they got abilities from both &quot;parent&quot; classes. Hybrids got some useful spells for a change, and archery became useful. Warriors got some small upgrades with AA as well; it is unfortunate that most of the AA that benefits them is in Archetype skills. However they still remain ahead of hybrids in HP and AC, and are only behind Monks for mitigation (reducing damage from, or avoiding, hits).<br>
<br>
<br>
No disadvantages to Hybrids you say?<br>
<br>
Just for starters, let's look at the situation most characters face since they're not in high-end guilds: Hybrids still have the undeserved reputation for sucking that their suckage earned during Kunark. Thus very few want hybrids in lower end guilds or experience groups.<br>
<br>
Speaking of what most players face, instead of the small fraction of those in high end guilds...<br>
<br>
Warriors have vastly more HP and AC without the ability to do high end encounters, and Defensive puts them far and above hybrids in 95% of all situations in the game in ability to soak up damage. Warriors might not be able to solo... but for 95% of the game, they get chosen in exp groups and for raid MTing over hybrids several levels above them.<br>
<br>
The 5% of Warriors who are in high-end guilds may have some problems.... but fixing these could mess up balance for the rest of the earlier stages of the game. I'm sure VI will adress the issues eventually, but with their usual shoddy work and rushed patches they will unbalance things in favor of Warriors again.<br>
<br>
Slay Undead:<br>
<br>
Yes, nice eye candy. However, its use is incredibly limited by the lack of enough undead encounters. And while it does make Paladins gods soloing undead, so what? You have to wait till 59 (preferably 60) to get it, and warriors will still do more damage because the non-slays in between the Slay hits are for lower damage than a Warrior would do with comparable weapons.<br>
<br>
2hers: Again, don't forget that while Hybrids put out some good damage and aggro with these, Warriors can also use many of the same 2hers but with higher offensive skills, and thus more effectively.<br>
<br>
