<br>
Yes, they do. Hybrids with lower skills (obviously not Rangers /glare Trueshot+Endless Quiver+AM3+Fleeting Quiver+30 or higher damage bow) miss out on a lot of DPS.<br>
<br>
Class AA skills: At least many of the Paladin class AA are useless, not just Warriors. Divine Stun: Was originally a passive ability to make stuns affect up to level 60 MoBs instead of 55- only. Was at first broken, then was changed to an instant stun that doesn't work on 55+ MoBs and re-use time of something like 1/2 hour. Double Riposte: Not really useful, been parsed at an obscenely low amount of extra damage. Mass Group Buff: Yeah, right. We get all of ONE spell that this will even affect. And it really ticks off Rangers. 2hand bash: *Almost* useful, since Pal/SK use 2h weapons most of the time. Adds an incredibly low amount of DPS--possibly useful if you fight lots of caster MoBs who are at least 10 levels below you. Act of Valor: Same cycle as Lay Hands. Since Lay Hands doesn't kill you, it's more desired, especially once you get improved LH. Improved LH: Useful, instant CHeal. Fearless: Useless... you'll be resisting anyway. Holy Steed: Maybe semi-useful, 20-30 hours of grinding for a decent horse. Slay Undead: As I mentioned, eye candy against uncommon MoBs only. Physical Enhancement: Useful. Warriors should have this, there is no reason why not.<br>
<br>
The archetype abilities are shared between Warriors and Pal/SK, Pal/SK just get archetype from their caster side as well.<br>
<br>
And everyone knows about general AA.<br>
<br>
<br>
A few thoughts:<br>
<br>
Perhaps warriors could use a bit of help--if taunt really works as little as you say, it needs fixing. Perhaps give it as much aggro as Cease + Desist, or at least as much as a single cast of Stun (those are the first 3 Paladin stuns) as well as the current effect, and make it work 95% against blues/ltblue, 100% against green (cmon, what's wrong with always having aggro on greenies?), 90% against even, and at level 60, 85% against anything above you. Byebye to a significant chunk of aggro problems. Cease and Desist are nice aggro. Triple attack should probably work more often, perhaps make it independant of whether or not double attack goes off.<br>
<br>
And just for more eye candy, warriors could get a new class AA:<br>
<br>
Maxxorz eye candy: Type: Passive. Increase critical frequency by 5% (1) to 10% (2) to 15% (3). (in addition to Combat Fury and innate chance to crit). Cost: 3 pts. per level, up to level 3.<br>
Biggzorz eye candy: Type: Passive. Increase critical damage by 10%. Cost: 3 pts.<br>
<br>
These would of course affect crips as well, and have better names.<br>
<br>
Maybe even this:<br>
<br>
Proc madness: Type: Active. Quad hit and proc weapons every time for a short duration (10 sec?). Long reuse timer. Cost: 9 pts.<br>
<br>
Or this:<br>
<br>
Foul mouth: Type: Active. Taunt works every time for 1 minute. 15 minute re-use? Longer? Cost: 8 pts.<br>
<br>
Even:<br>
<br>
Insult parents: Type: Active. MoB has only the warrior on hate list for 3-5 minutes. Reuse: Long. Cost: 9 pts.<br>
<br>
Not all of these of course. Just some ideas. And I would be in heaven with:<br>
<br>
Charm clueless: Type: Active. You Dire Charm a clueless member of the group, and can control its actions like you control your own character. Cost: 1 pt.<br>
