Yeah, Verant screwed Tanks on the Class AA...but remember, as many have already stated: Warriors used to be the BEST tanking melee. Somehow I find it sad that when a class is SOOO far ahead of others, they forget what parity is, and how it feels to be &quot;Just another melee&quot;. Other melee classes have been upgraded to close the gap between Warriors and all the rest. Sorry if that is hurting any feelings, but really you had it good for a long time. And its still really not bad. Again, I have yet to see any other classes MT on boss mobs &amp; heavy encounters. XP groups? Too bad, get in line with everyone else. A raid can be cancelled if no Warriors show up, would be a pity to not be able to get regular XP without a Tank.<br>
<br>
The Renjer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchronnos1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chronnos1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 12:49:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=338>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Ideally...</span><hr size=1> Ideally, if Verant ever did plan on making mitigation/avoidance changes to the game like they did with melee &quot;balancing&quot; of damage in Velious, theres a few things they can do. Unfortunately, there would also need to be some major MOB retuning because a lot of encounters will be too trivial under these changes.<br>
<br>
My idea would be (and some of this was taken from other posts) to 1st make tiered classes due to mitigation and then avoidance.<br>
<br>
For mitigation -<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Heavy Plate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Warriors, Paladins, and Shadowknights. Easy way to fix the mitigation is to raise the AC softcap to 1600 or so, with Combat Stability 3. Or 1450 without any CS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Light Plate</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Bards and clerics. Since bards also get CS, their max mitigation would be 1400, including CS3. Clerics max mitigation would be 1250, which is right around where the current AC softcap is for Warriors and knights.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Chain</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Shamans, Rangers, and Rogues. Their max mitigation with CS3 (for rangers and rogues) would be 1250 (As good as clerics), or 1100 without any CS. Also Shamans max mitigation would be 1100.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Leather classes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Druids and monks. Their max mitigation with CS would be around max 1150 or 1000 ac without any CS (like druids). This makes them weaker than chain classes on the mitigation side, unless monks train in CS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Cloth classes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Wizards, Necros, Mages, Enchanters. Their max mitigation cap would be around 800ac (which I think thats what it is now).<br>
<br>
As for Avoidance (its a lot harder to classify avoidance as to a number) - <br>
<br>
1) Monks - monks should be the most nimble class in game, due to their light armor and class description<br>
2)Rogues and Rangers - Rogues/Rangers are somewhat the equivalent to monks in terms of their nimbleness, yet wear chain armor and have somewhat higher mitigation. This makes it so that their avoidance is less than monks, because of the higher armor they wear.<br>
3)Warriors - Warriors, even though they wear heavy plate, should be very close to Rogues and Rangers in their nimbleness due to their job of taking hits.<br>
4)Knights - Knights, being somewhat equivalents to warriors, have less avoidance due to the fact that they aren't as accustomed to taking damage and rely on spellcasting to augment that fact<br>
5)Shamans, bards, and druids<br>
6)clerics, and robed casters<br>
<br>
Now, if these were tiered like that in game, there wouldn't be any question of who is better than who in terms of tanking. The steps to repair mitigation are extremely easy to fix, just raise the stupid ac caps in that tiered fashion for the alotted classes.<br>
<br>
Also, another idea - Lots and lots of knights and some warriors want a reason to wear a shield. One viable option is to give warriors and knights the &quot;block&quot; skill when they equip a shield <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  only</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. This would allow our avoidance to be better at the cost of damage potential, since shields don't do much damage.<br>
<br>
As far as taunting power goes - warrior's taunt skill sorely need to be revisited. The fact that you need to AA exp and acquire certain weapons acknowledges the fact that taunt in its current form is broken. Don't get me wrong, I like how I can taunt easily anywhere without any problems as a Paladin, but that shouldn't be the case. Warriors need to be able to taunt almost as effectively as me on exp mobs. Personally, thats where I see most of the problem with warriors in exp groups. A Paladin or Shadowknights Utility in an exp group is nice, but nowhere near the most desired aspect of why we get groups. Its the taunting potential of keeping casters from not getting hit in zones like Cazic Thule, deep Chardok, and Ssra (exp camps) is why knights are preferred. Fix taunt for warriors in exp groups by making the taunt ability add more hate each time its pressed. Its not hard.<br>
<br>
For raids - taunt shouldn't be touched at all for both warriors and Paladins. Although, I would definitely wish SKs had something almost as powerful as disease cloud in their lineup to keep taunt going strong, because their taunt isn't as nearly effective now as it was.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  In summary</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Change the AC softcaps of all classes into a tiered system of heavy plate, light plate, chain classes, etc. Change avoidance tables to adjust accordingly. Make shields viable again for knights and warriors by giving us a block ability with shield equipped. Finally, fix warrior taunt in exp groups (in a non-equipment and non-AA way) so they can keep a mob on them and not on the casters.<br>
<br>
Edit: For those wondering where the difference in tanking between a warrior and Paladin will come from - it will be from the difference in avoindance (should be quite different), difference in hitpoints, and better availability of AC items to push to the cap along with items to balance their hps currently. Possibly, if thats not enough, then knights can get their AC cap scaled down 50 or so points. But this idea is a start <p><center>-<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=100602>Chronnos Planeswalker</a>
 60th Crusader of Tunare- </center>

